Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper describes the development of a translation system using neural encoder-decoder architecture with attention mechanism. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is also likely as the paper focuses on speech translation systems. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper uses machine learning techniques for developing the end-to-end model. 
- cs.LG (Learning) is a possible category as the paper investigates the impact of training with heterogeneous corpora and target tokenization. 
- cs.SI (Speech and Audio Processing) is another possible category as the paper deals with speech input segmentation.
